<DOC><DOCNO> AP880215-0214 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-15-88 0820EST</FILEID><FIRST>a a BC-History Adv26   02-15 0372</FIRST><SECOND>BC-History, Adv 26,0389</SECOND><NOTE>$adv26</NOTE><NOTE>For Release Friday, Feb. 26</NOTE><HEAD>Today in History</HEAD><HEAD>By The Associated Press</HEAD><TEXT>   Today is Friday, Feb. 26, the 57th day of 1988. There are 309days left in the year.   Today's Highlight in History:   On Feb. 26, 1919, Congress established Grand Canyon NationalPark in Arizona.   On this date:   In 1802, one of the great figures of French literature, VictorHugo, was born in Besancon.   In 1815, Napoleon Bonaparte escaped from the Island of Elba tobegin his second conquest of France.   In 1846, ``Buffalo Bill'' Cody was born near Davenport, Iowa.   In 1848, the Second French Republic was proclaimed.   In 1870, the first New York City subway line was opened to thepublic.   In 1942, during World War II, Navy flier Donald F. Mason sent afour-word message from the Pacific to the U.S. Navy in Washington:``Sighted sub, sank same.''   In 1951, the 22nd Amendment to the Constitution was ratified,limiting a President to two terms in office.   In 1952, Prime Minister Winston S. Churchill announced thatBritain had developed its own atomic bomb.   In 1962, after becoming the first American to orbit the Earth,John Glenn told a joint meeting of Congress, ``exploration and thepursuit of knowledge have always paid dividends in the long run.''   Ten years ago: Israel's Cabinet voted to continue its limitedpolicy of establishing settlements in occupied territories,specifically authorizing three new settlements in the West Bank.   Five years ago: Britain's Queen Elizabeth II and her husband,Prince Philip, arrived in San Diego Bay for a 10-day West Coasttour that included a Hollywood banquet and visits with PresidentReagan and his wife, Nancy.   One year ago: The Tower commission, appointed by PresidentReagan to probe the Iran-Contra affair, issued its report, whichrebuked the president for failing to control his national securitystaff.   Today's Birthdays: Actor Mason Adams is 69. Actor Tony Randallis 68. Actress Betty Hutton is 67. Singer Fats Domino is 60.Columnist Robert Novak is 57. Singer Johnny Cash is 56.   Thought for Today: ``The secret of my success is that at anearly age I discovered I was not God.'' _ Oliver Wendell HolmesJr., U.S. Supreme Court Justice (1841-1935).</TEXT><NOTE>End Adv</NOTE></DOC>